"""
adding Gaussing distribution to anti proton data array
"""

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statistics
from numpy import array
import pandas as pd
import random
pd.set_option('display.float_format', lambda x: '%0.4f' % x)

data = []

"""
Read data from total data file
--------------------
"""
print("Reading data ...")
data = array(pd.read_table("/Users/jiancheng/GRAMS/Toy Model/data/cut/TOF_anti_proton_1e7_0_500_45_4_result.txt", delimiter=" "))
print("finish reading data!")
pbar = data

print(type(data[1, 0]))
print(type(data))
print(data)

sigma = 0.1    #energy resolution percentage
deltaT = 0    #timing resolution/ns

time_pbar_err = np.array([None] * len(data[:,0]))
dEOut_pbar_err = np.array([None] * len(data[:,0]))
dEIn_pbar_err = np.array([None] * len(data[:,0]))

for i in range(len(data[:,0])):
    dEOut_pbar_err[i] = random.gauss(data[i, 0], sigma * data[i, 0])
    dEIn_pbar_err[i] = random.gauss(data[i, 1], sigma * data[i, 1])
    time_pbar_err[i] = data[i, 2] + deltaT * 2 * (random.random() - 0.5)
    print("applying error:"+str(int(100*i/len(data[:,0])))+"%", end='\r')

plt.scatter(time_pbar_err, dEOut_pbar_err, marker = '.', color = 'b', label = 'TOF out layer')
plt.scatter(time_pbar_err, dEIn_pbar_err, marker = '.', color = 'r', label = 'TOF inner layer')
plt.title('anti proton TOF with error')
plt.xlabel('Time [ns]')
plt.ylabel('Energy diposit')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')
#plt.axis([0, 20, 0, 10])
plt.grid(alpha = 0.2)
plt.show()

low_limit = 11
high_limit = 12

"""
antiproton
"""
pbar_out = dEOut_pbar_err[np.logical_and(time_pbar_err>low_limit, time_pbar_err<high_limit)]
pbar_in = dEIn_pbar_err[np.logical_and(time_pbar_err>low_limit, time_pbar_err<high_limit)]

pbar_x_min = np.min(pbar_out)
pbar_x_max = np.max(pbar_out)

pbar_y_min = np.min(pbar_in)
pbar_y_max = np.max(pbar_in)

pbar_x_bins = np.linspace(pbar_x_min,pbar_x_max,100)
pbar_y_bins = np.linspace(pbar_y_min,pbar_y_max,100)

"""
antiHe3
"""
He3bar_out = dEOut_He3bar_err[np.logical_and(time_He3bar_err>low_limit, time_He3bar_err<high_limit)]
He3bar_in = dEIn_He3bar_err[np.logical_and(time_He3bar_err>low_limit, time_He3bar_err<high_limit)]

He3bar_x_min = np.min(He3bar_out)
He3bar_x_max = np.max(He3bar_out)

He3bar_y_min = np.min(He3bar_in)
He3bar_y_max = np.max(He3bar_in)

He3bar_x_bins = np.linspace(He3bar_x_min,He3bar_x_max,100)
He3bar_y_bins = np.linspace(He3bar_y_min,He3bar_y_max,100)

xmin = min(*pbar_out, *He3bar_out)
xmax = max(*pbar_out, *He3bar_out)
ymin = min(*pbar_in, *He3bar_in)
ymax = max(*pbar_in, *He3bar_in)
ext = (xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
hist1 = plt.hexbin(pbar_out, pbar_in, gridsize=100, bins = 100, cmap='Reds', mincnt=0, alpha=0.6, extent=ext, label = "anti proton 45 degree")
hist2 = plt.hexbin(He3bar_out, He3bar_in, gridsize=100, bins = 100,  cmap='Blues', mincnt=0, alpha=0.5, extent=ext, label = "anti He3 45 degree")
plt.colorbar(hist1, orientation='vertical')
plt.colorbar(hist2, orientation='vertical')

plt.title("0 degree with 30 percent E error")

start_time = 7
low_limit = 10
high_limit = 11
for n in range(12):
    N_x = []
    N_y = []
    He3bar_cut_x = []
    He3bar_cut_y = []
    plt.cla()
    cut_min_x = np.max(dEOut_pbar_err[np.logical_and(time_pbar_err>start_time+n, time_pbar_err<start_time+n+1)]) 
    cut_min_y = np.max(dEIn_pbar_err[np.logical_and(time_pbar_err>start_time+n, time_pbar_err<start_time+n+1)])
    He3bar_cut_x = dEOut_He3bar_err[np.logical_and(time_He3bar_err>start_time+n, time_He3bar_err<start_time+n+1)]
    He3bar_cut_y = dEIn_He3bar_err[np.logical_and(time_He3bar_err>start_time+n, time_He3bar_err<start_time+n+1)]
    N_x = He3bar_cut_x[np.logical_not(np.logical_and(He3bar_cut_x<cut_min_x, He3bar_cut_y<cut_min_y))]
    N_y = He3bar_cut_y[np.logical_not(np.logical_and(He3bar_cut_x<cut_min_x, He3bar_cut_y<cut_min_y))]
    plt.scatter(N_x, N_y)
    plt.title("0 degree incoming TOF time between [{}".format(start_time+n)+", {}".format(start_time + 1 +n)+"]ns")
    plt.show()
    print("Outer TOF cut:"+str(cut_min_x))
    print("Inner TOF cut:"+str(cut_min_y))
    print("cut efficiency:"+str(len(N_x)/(len(He3bar_cut_x)+1)))
